Detailed Description

cvmx_sriomaint::_lcs_ba0

MSBs of SRIO address space mapped to maintenance BAR. The double word aligned SRIO address window mapped to the SRIO maintenance BAR. This window has the highest priority and eclipses matches to the BAR0, BAR1 and BAR2 windows. Note: Address bits not supplied in the transfer are considered zero. For example, SRIO address 65:35 must be set to zero to match in a 34-bit access. SRIO address 65:50 must be set to zero to match in a 50-bit access. This coding allows the maintenance bar window to appear in specific address spaces. The remaining bits are located in SRIOMAINT()_LCS_BA1. This SRIO maintenance BAR is effectively disabled when LCSBA[30] is set with 34 or 50-bit addressing.
